<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Firms Advised Not To Shy Away from Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- German companies should not be
hesitant or reluctant to invest aggressively in Asia because of
the financial crisis, but rather to move forward and exploit new
opportunities, a leading German industry group said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Bonn, the umbrella organization of
German industrial lobby groups and the chambers of commerce, known
as the DIHT, said that German companies should do everything
possible to survive the Asian crisis without contemplating a
retreat from the region.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot abandon the market position that we have built up
over the recent years," the DIHT said.
</P>
<P>
It also observed that opportunities had emerged in Asia
especially for German companies that have local production
facilities there for exports. There were now many more chances to
buy into local companies or to increase holdings, the DIHT said.
</P>
</TEXT>
