<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Holds Talks with PM of Luxembourg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 27 (Xinhua) -- President Boris Yeltsin Tuesday
met with visiting Prime Minister of Luxembourg Jean-Claude
Juncker, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Yeltsin called for a European security charter
jointly worked out by the Europeans.
</P>
<P>
The two men agreed that there can be no difference between the
future of Europe and the future of Russia, which had to be built
together.
</P>
<P>
On the Iraq problem, Yeltsin said that Russia firmly supports
political and diplomatic efforts to settle the latest problems
there.
</P>
<P>
On Russia's domestic situation, Yeltsin said he is convinced
that a president capable of guaranteeing democratic development
should be elected in the next elections in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Juncker said Europe was satisfied with the many positive
results occurring in Russia in 1997, including the stability of
the ruble, record low inflation, privatization and growing
political stability.
</P>
<P>
Juncker talked about the steps taken by the Luxembourg
government to enhance ties in economy and finance between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, he also met his Russian counterpart Viktor
Chernomyrdin. The two leaders signed cooperation agreements for
1998 in health care, medical science and the pharmaceutical
industry 1998.
</P>
<P>
Juncker arrived here on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
