Nearly 20,000 passengers are expected to get in or out of the
terminal building daily on peak days, a spokesman for the Civil
Aviation Department said.
</P>
<P>
More than 350 extra flights will be operated between January 26
and February 4, according to the latest information from airlines.
The airport will have handle about 465 flights a day, 35 more than
on a normal busy day. (Hong Kong-Residents-New Year)
