<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Plane Crash in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen persons including three
foreigners were killed and 20 others injured in a Myanmar
passenger plane crash in Thandwe, Rakhine state of Myanmar, at
11:45 hours (local time) Tuesday, the official Myanmar News Agency
reported Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The Fokker-27 aircraft of the state-run Myanmar Airways ran
into a wall at the Thandwe Airport while attempting to take off.
The accident took place due to a sudden failure of the machine,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Among the killed are two French (a man and a woman) and an
Italian man and one of the injured is also a foreigner.
</P>
<P>
There were 41 passengers and four crews on board the plane, the
report added.
</P>
<P>
Rescue work is under way.  
</P>
</TEXT>
