<HEADLINE> Abright to Visit Europe over Iraq Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 27 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will travel to Europe on Wednesday to
coordinate with key foreign ministers on crisis with Iraq, U.S.
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Albright is expected to meet Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov in Madrid, French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine in
Paris and British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook in London.
</P>
<P>
The secretary of state plans to inform her counterparts about
a possible American bombing campaign against Iraq, according to
a United Press International (UPI) report.
</P>
<P>
Details of the trip were still being worked out, and he did not
rule out that Albright might travel on from Europe to the Middle
East, said a senior official who asked not to be identified.
</P>
<P>
Consultations would deal with "next steps" on Iraq which has
defied the United Nations by barring its arms inspectors from
certain sites and by refusing to cooperate with an inspection team
led by an American.
</P>
<P>
Washington warned on Monday that time for diplomatic solution
to the crisis is running out and may launch a military strike
against Iraq when necessary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
