<HEADLINE> Greece to Lodge Protest Against Turkish Violation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Greece would lodge a protest
against Monday's violation of rules of safe passage by Turkish
torpedoes boats inside Greek territorial waters in the Aegean Sea,
a Greek government official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas described the incident as "not common and
dangerous" for peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Two Turkish torpedoes boats entered Monday Greek waters west of
the uninhabited Imia island, and their crews fired weapons at sea,
according to Greek Foreign Ministry sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the vessels returned to the Turkish side
only after a patroling Greek gunboat warned them of the violation
of the maritime safety rules and asked them to leave the Greek
waters.
</P>
<P>
Greek-Turkish relations have been deteriorated in recent months
and some Greek officials do not rule out the possibility of a
conflict between the two countries in the Aegean Sea in the
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
