<HEADLINE> Mrs. Mitterand Calls for Solution to Immigration Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Danielle Mitterrand, wife of the
late French President Francois Mitterrand, Tuesday urged Europe to
formulate a policy in order to resolve the immigration problem.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, Mrs. Mitterrand said that
the question was not whether Western countries wanted to or were
able to have these immigrants in Europe, but to give them the
opportunity to return to their homes without any problems.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Mitterrand, also president of the "France Libertes"
foundation, is currently in Greece to attend a conference on
"Racism against Democracy" held in Athens by the Institute for
Strategic and Developmental Study (ISTAME) - Andreas Papandreou.
</P>
<P>
For the past years, they had been condemning the genocide being
perpetrated against the Kurdish people, she said, adding that
their mission today was to attack the true cause of this
catastrophe, to protect the people and to offer them their
solidarity.
</P>
<P>
She also said that measures taken by European countries to curb
unemployment should not be turned against immigrants because such
policies could result in Racism.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Mitterrand today also met with the Greek leadership
including President Costis Stephanopoulos and Prime Minister
Costas Simitis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
