<HEADLINE> Bad Weather Affects Transport in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Heavy snowfall and Gale-force
winds have caused serious transport problems throughout Greece.
</P>
<P>
All coastal shipping from the ports of Piraeus and Rafina to
the islands of the Aegean, the Dodecanese and Crete, was suspended
due to the gale-force winds in the Aegean Sea, according to the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Heavy snow, most in mountainous regions, is also falling in the
western Peloponnese Peninsula, isolating several villages around
Kosmas and Aghios Petros as well the Tripoli-Argos road via
Ahladokambos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
