<HEADLINE> Russia, Luxembourg Sign Agreements on Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Russian and Luxembourg Prime
Ministers, Viktor Chernomyrdin and Jean-Claude Juncker, signed
three intergovernmental agreements on bilateral cooperations in
Moscow on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Itar-Tass, these agreements include an
agreement on cooperation in health care, medical aid and the
medical industry, an intergovernmental program of cultural and
scientific cooperation for 1998-2000 and an interbank agreement on
cooperation in the training of bank personnel.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Chernomyrdin said that "We have
plenty of chances to increase the potential of cooperation between
Russia and Luxembourg, especially in the trade and economic
cooperation and the sphere of businesses."
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin expressed satisfaction with his negotiations with
Juncker. He said Russia "values high the Luxembourg support to the
Russian admission to the European Union." The agreement signed
just now, the Russian premier said, "will give a fresh impetus to
our future cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Juncker said that good relations between Russia and Luxembourg
are a historical tradition. It is clear that Russia and the
European Union will keep pace with each other in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Juncker arrived here on Tuesday for an official visit. He had
talks with Russian President Boris Yeltsin on the same day.
</P>
</TEXT>
