on Wednesday it had selected the northwestern Alpine city of Turin
as the Italian candidate for the 2006 Winter Games.
</P>
<P>
Turin collected 23 votes at the Committee's national council
meeting, beating the rival bid Venice on 13 votes.
</P>
<P>
Turin's bid foresees investments of 1.934 trillion lire (about
1.09 billion U.S. Dollars), including a cost of 15 billion lire
(84 million Dollars) for a special structure built for speed
skating in the 70,000 capacity Delle Alpi stadium.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee is due to decide on the
venue for the 2006 Games at a meeting in Seoul in September 1999.
