<HEADLINE> Tianjin Seeks Funding for Road Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, a major port city in
northern China, will require funding of 10 billion yuan (1.2
billion US dollars) over the next three years to improve its urban
highway network.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used mainly for the construction of eight
expressways stretching several hundred kilometers, according to a
local official.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the municipality will rely mainly on
state and local government funding, but will also seek funds from
diversified sources in order to complete the ambitious plan.
</P>
<P>
One method centers on strictly evaluating the existing roads
which will be repaired or rebuilt, with a second approach centered
on finding foreign partners to join in cooperative projects to
upgrade existing roads or undertake new construction projects.
</P>
<P>
Other methods include using World Bank loans, BOT (build,
operate, transfer) or granting exclusive operational rights.
</P>
<P>
The plan has attracted the interest of investors from Hong
Kong, Canada and Italy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
