<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Hong Kong into Lunar New Year Soccer Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Nigeria
defeated Asian power Iran 1-0 while a Hong Kong League XI side
downed the Chilean national team 3-1 in the 1998 Carlsberg Cup
Lunar New Year soccer tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
1998 is the Year of Tiger according to the Lunar calendar.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria will then play host Hong Kong in the championship tite
clash this weekend while Iran and Chile, the two losers of the
opening matches on Wednesday, will meet on the same day for the
third place of the annual two-day tournament.
</P>
<P>
Garba Ahmed scored Nigeria's lone goal at the 50th minute,
after a goalless first half.
</P>
<P>
Chile's only goal was scored by Rodrigo Barrera at the eighth
minute while Hong Kong League Selection's equalizer was put in by
Joakim Grandelius at the 13th minute.
</P>
<P>
Paul Anthony Foster was the local hero as he made it two at the
34th and 89th minutes, which made the local fans at the Hong Kong
Stadium jump for joy.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's newly-appointed Brazilian coach Sebastiao Pereira
Araujo fielded an all-foreign line-up on Wednesday, which came as
totally unexpected. He wanted a best possible side ever available
for the Lunar New Year celebrations, he had so explained for his
choice.
</P>
<P>
"If we could play as well as today, we could beat Nigeria,
Chile or Iran," the satisfied Araujo claimed after Hong Kong's
victory over Chile.
</P>
<P>
But he will need some magic if he wishes to beat a much
stronger and tougher Nigerian team, winner of the Atlanta Olympic
Games, three days later in the final.
</P>
<P>
Chile, Iran and Nigeria, all qualifiers for the World Cup
finals in coming June in France, are playing here without their
top draw cards. But their line-ups were still as impressive as
they did in the World Cup qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
Nigaria's newly-appointed Yugoslav-born coach Bora Milutinovic
has brought here a young side which he said would be "future
stars". "They might not be very known now, but they'll be after
the World Cup," he said.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic has set winning the Carlsberg Cup as his first
mission on the new job. And he had played down the absense of
some big-name European-based professionals on the squard.
</P>
<P>
He had admitted that he knew little about his Super Eagles
side. "It is impossible to change the style with such little time
as I'm just getting to know the players. But what is important is
that they can all play well," he added. 
</P>
