<HEADLINE> France Criticizes UNSCOM Chief's Remarks on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 28 (Xinhua) -- France Wednesday criticized the
remarks made by Richard Butler, Chairman of the United Nations
Special Commission on disarmament in Iraq, that Iraq owns enough
biological and chemical weapons to blow up Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
"This is not exactly what comes out of the reports of the
Special Commission in charge of disarmament in Iraq (UNSCOM), and
I wonder if he (Butler) has gone too far from his role," said
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
At a conference organized by American Jewish organizations in
New York Tuesday, Butler declared that Iraq possesses missiles
carrying bacillus dust and botulismotoxin which are capable of
annihilating the population of Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux said Butler's
declaration does not conform with information sent by UNSCOM to
the United Nations Security Council.
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Butler was not in his role when he made such estimations,"
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The French ambassador to the United Nations, Alain Dejammet,
who has resumed the rotating presidency of the Security Council,
will express his concern over the declaration by Butler to the
United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan, said French
diplomatic sources. 
</P>
