<HEADLINE> Bidding System Proves Effective in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 28 (Xinhua) -- The bidding system has yielded
economic results in the purchase of equipment in central China's
Hunan Province, according to local government sources.
</P>
<P>
The province introduced the system a decade ago in purchasing
equipment for capital construction and technical innovation
projects.
</P>
<P>
By now, the bidding system has been introduced in the purchase
of 200 million US dollars' equipment from outside China and of 200
million yuan's equipment from inside China for 180 projects in the
province.
</P>
<P>
An equivalent of some 300 million yuan was saved during the
purchase of the equipment, government officials said.
</P>
<P>
For example, the Xiangtan Iron and Steel Corporation saved 2.1
million US dollars by accepting open bidding for imported steel
wire.
</P>
<P>
Open bidding has also effectively prevented corruption and
helped build clean government. 
</P>
