<HEADLINE> Xi'an Opens '98 China Tourism Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 28 (Xinhua) -- The opening ceremony for the '98
China Tourism Year was held in Xi'an, capital of northwest China's
Shaanxi Province today, as local people celebrated the beginning
of the Spring Festival, the traditional Chinese New Year.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was held at Weiyang Lake, an amusement park in the
eastern suburbs of Xi'an. The ceremony, held amidst red lanterns
and colorful flags, drew thousands of local residents and
tourists. The event featured various dances, stage performances
and fireworks display.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Province is a popular tourism destination and Xi'an one
of four major Chinese cities attracting foreign tourists.
</P>
<P>
Kong Qingsen, director of the province's tourism bureau, said
the city attracted more than 25 million domestic and foreign
tourists in 1997, up nine percent on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province will focus on several tourism projects, including
a drum festival, ice sculpture and rural folk paintings
exhibitions, a marathon, rock climbing, and desert tours,
according to the director. 
</P>
