<HEADLINE> Xiamen Witnesses Rebound in Foreign Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen in east China's Fujian
Province rebounded in 1997 from a three year decline in
foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city approved 460 foreign-funded
projects in 1997, up 22.67 percent on 1996. Their total
investments climbed 1.64 percent to 1.89 billion U.S. dollars,
with 1.3 billion U.S. dollars acturally used.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said the investments from the United States and
Europe jumped from 66 million U.S. dollars in 1996 to 596 million
U.S. dollars in 1997, registering an increase of eight times.
</P>
<P>
Some 72.8 percent of the 460 foreign-funded projects approved
last year was on the manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investments in the service industry in the city also
increased last year, with foreign investors shying away from the
real estate sector.
</P>
<P>
</P>
