<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Parade, Fiesta Start off Tiger Year in HK (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Together in the parade, some 15 floats designed around two
themes -- "Traditional Chinese New Year" and "Modern Hong Kong" --
were a one-of-a-kind spectacle.
</P>
<P>
Some of the designs celebrated a new beginning, like "The Year
of the Tiger," which features the New Year mascot, and "Bauhinia
Flowers in Blossom," which represents a new era for Hong Kong.
Others, such as the Hong Kong Tourism Association's float,
"Dynamic Hong Kong," "HK -- The World of Telecommunications" and
"The World's Treasure Chest," celebrated Hong Kong as a vibrant
and cosmopolitan city.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands spectators along the parade route were
dazzled by local performers, including stunt cyclists and a
mini-rugby demonstration team, as well as international acts such
as an award-winning mummers parade, a renowned cheerleading team,
a traditional cloth horse dance troupe, drummers from Japan, Samba
dancers, and folk dancers from South Korea and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
"This colorful parade and fiesta enables us to share the
excitement and joy of this special time of year with people from
all around the world, as well as promote Hong Kong as a major
center for Chinese New Year festivities," Executive Director of
the Hong Kong Tourism Association Amy Chan said. "Large-scale
events such as this one enhance Hong Kong's image as the Events
Capital of Asia," he added.
</P>
<P>
The parade was followed by a two-day fiesta, which started at
16:30 (GMT 08:30) at the Centenary Garden. Eight floats were on
display, enabling the public to take a closer look at the
craftsmanship that went into their creation.
</P>
<P>
Later in the evening, Virginia Yung, Miss Hong Kong, is
expected to take part in the official "Lighting-up Ceremony" which
will not only illuminate all the floats but the entire garden.
</P>
<P>
The more than 20 stalls and booths, with fortune-tellers,
refreshments and arts and crafts, and an array of live stage
performances, created and are creating a lively and fun
atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
According to a local official admiring the party, more than 300
retail outlets and restaurants stay open over the traditional
Chinese New Year holiday this year against that in the past years
when almost such outlets and restaurants were closed over such a
holiday.
</P>
<P>
"We feel that our support over the Chinese New Year is a useful
step to strengthening Hong Kong's position as one of the world's
most popular travel destinations," said a restaurateur.  
</P>
