cents late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The general sentiment seems to be on the upside," Nick
Volanakis, Colonial State Bank foreign exchange trader said.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar would need to keep up the momentum to
break through 68 US cents, he said.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the local unit began the day on a stronger note,
aided by a rise in the price of gold, improving Asian currencies
and a depressed US dollar.
</P>
