<HEADLINE> Sustainable Economic Growth Proceeds in Northwest China Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 28 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product
(GDP) in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region has been
estimated at 21 billion yuan (2.6 billion U.S. dollars) for 1997,
said Ma Qizhi, chairman of the autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
This represents a rise of 7.5 percent over the previous year,
but 1.3 percent lower than the national level.
</P>
<P>
Though an undeveloped and inland region, Ningxia obtained 1.36
billion yuan (170 million U.S. dollars) of revenue for the year,
increasing by 12.1 percent over 1996, according to Ma.
</P>
<P>
Ma said the region's foreign trade grew rapidly in 1997, with
the total import and export volume estimated at 290 million
U.S. dollars, an increase of 23.9 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The region has promoted technological and economic cooperation
with the country's coastal areas. It introduced 110 million yuan
(13.7 million U.S. dollars) from the coastal areas and completed
65 cooperative projects.
</P>
<P>
Because of close attention paid to the construction of farmland
and water conservation, the region's 1997 grain output could
reach 2.57 billion kg in 1997, he said.
</P>
<P>
The per capita net income of rural residents in the region
should reach 1,540 yuan (192.5 U.S. dollars) in the year, a real
growth of some 7 percent, he said. And 200,000 farmers have risen
above the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the region's fixed-asset investment reached 8.5
billion yuan, a 10 percent increase compared with 1996.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen company groups have been set up in 1997, and 68.5
percent of small state-run enterprises have completed their system
transformation.
</P>
<P>
Looking ahead toward 1998, the region should maintain its
steady economic growth, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
