Karthikeyan, who headed the special investigation team (SIT) of
CBI which probed the May 21, 1991 killing of Rajiv Gandhi at an
election rally in Tamil Nadu's Sriperumbudur, told newsmen that
the nation stands vindicated Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
All the 26 accused have been charged with conspiring and
facilitating the assassination of Rajiv Gandhi.
</P>
<P>
The SIT of the CBI, which conducted the high-profile probe into
the meticulously planned killing of Rajiv Gandhi, carried out by a
woman suicide bomber, has produced evidence during the prolonged
trial seeking to show the involvement of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) supremo Velupillai Prabhakaran in the
conspiracy.  
