will lay focus on the need to activate the European role mainly
that of Britain in pushing forward the staggering peace process in
the region and getting it out of the present stalemate because of
the Israeli government's intransigent policies.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also review recent Arab and African
proposals to resolve the Libya-West crisis and the importance of
reaching a political and diplomatic solution for the crisis
between Iraq and the U.N. within the context of a commitment to
the relevant international legitimacy resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Libya has been debilitated by a six-year international embargo
imposed on it for refusing to hand over the Libyan suspects in the
1988 bombing of a Pan-Am jet over Lockerbie, Scotland. Britain and
the U.S. insisted on having them tried on their territories.
</P>
<P>
Iraq, locked in an escalating standoff with the U.N. over its
weapons inspections, have demanded a recomposition of the
U.N. inspection team which it said includes too many Britons and
Americans.
