in Kasese District, said the kids in camps for the displaced are
the most affected.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the high death rate to malnutrition. The
malnourished children are too weak to resist malaria, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Nurses in a local hospital said the medical staff of the
hospital were overwhelmed by the large number of patients. They
said they are forced to go off work at 02:00 a.m. instead of at
usual 06:00 p.m.
</P>
<P>
The children ward of the hospital admitted 65 patients instead
of usual 32, "The Monitor" paper said in its report.
</P>
<P>
