<HEADLINE> Guizhou Using Advanced Farming Techniques to Promote Grain Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Grain output of southwest
China's Guizhou Province reached 10.25 million tons in 1997
mainly due to the application of advanced farming techniques.
</P>
<P>
This figure represents an increase of 2 percent over 1996 and
an all-time high, said Sun Yizhong, an official of the Provincial
Agriculture Department.
</P>
<P>
Sun attributed the increase in grain output to the
popularization of advanced farming techniques.
</P>
<P>
He said that Guizhou in 1997 spread the use of 83 advanced
farming techniques. More than 10 million farmers received
technical training.
</P>
<P>
So far, half of the province's farmers -- eight million -- each
have grasped at least one farming technnique, according to Sun.
</P>
<P>
He said that the province has built 194,000 hectares of
terraced fields in the past five years, increasing grain
output by a total of 630 million kilograms.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the province has added 55,000 hectares of
irrigated farmland.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that the agricultural development has helped 5.45
million farmers shake off poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
