<HEADLINE> Pakistan PM to Visit Russia in April: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif will pay a three-day official visit to Russia in the
first week of April at the invitation of President Boris Yeltsin,
a local newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sharif will be the first Pakistani Prime Minister to visit
Russia after the disintegration of the former Soviet Union, Dawn
quoted diplomatic sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Dawn report said a formal invitation to Sharif was received
last year and officials of the two countries will finalize the
specific date of the visit next month.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Sharif will hold discussions with Russian
leaders on defense, gas sales, trade and economic cooperation as
well as international and regional issues, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan issue will top the agenda of the discussions, said
the report, adding that Sharif will brief the Russian leadership
on Pakistan's continued efforts for peace in Afghanistan in line
with the U.N. peace mission.
</P>
<P>
The report also said Pakistan is interested in purchasing the
Russian high-tech SU fighter aircraft and the MiG series besides
the Russian tank of the T-series.  
</P>
</TEXT>
