<HEADLINE> East China Province Reports Increased Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 28 (Xinhua) -- The grain output in east China's
Anhui Province reached 28.03 million tons in 1997, 1.29 million
tons more than 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province has reaped good grain harvests for three
consecutive years, according to local statistics.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, oil-bearing crops totaled 1.95 million tons;
meat, 2.66 million tons; and aquatic products, 1.3 million
tons. The cotton output was 301,000 tons, an increase of 11.5
percent over 1996.
</P>
