enterprises earned sales of 440 billion yuan (55 billion
U.S. dollars), up 19 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The per capita net income of local farmers is expected to top
1,800 yuan (225 U.S. dollars) in 1997, a rise of 11.3 percent over
1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province made great efforts to expand the use of
13 major agricultural techniques. And 12 million farmers and
cadres at grass-roots received technical training.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that improved varieties of crops have been used
on 89 percent of the province's farmland.  
