<HEADLINE> LTTE Launches Simultaneous Attacks on Military Camps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Large numbers of Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels launched three attacks on
military camps simultaneously in Eastern Sri Lanka Tuesday night,
military sources said Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Government troops repulsed the attack on one of the camps, an
Army brigade command, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
There have been no reports of casualties yet. But the sources
said the rebels involved in the attacks were in large numbers.
</P>
<P>
The attacks came only one day after the government announced it
outlawed the LTTE with immediate effect.
</P>
<P>
The government's decision to outlaw the LTTE followed Sunday
morning's fatal bomb explosion in Kandy, a central mountain city
where the 50th independence day celebrations had been scheduled to
take place on February 4.
</P>
<P>
However, the government decided this morning that the main
function in Kandy will be shifted to Colombo, while the planned
religious activities to mark the day will go ahead in Kandy.
</P>
<P>
A government official told Xinhua that the cabinet is holding a
meeting on the issue of celebration arrangements in Colombo.
</P>
<P>
No other details were available now.  
