<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Govt Cancels Independence Day Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 28 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
decided to cancel its scheduled independence day celebrations in
the ancient capital city of Kandy and hold the main function in
Colombo instead, a news release said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Capital Radio Station reported that the government issued a
news release this morning, saying that the celebrations to mark
the 50th independence day in Kandy will be canceled.
</P>
<P>
The main function will now be conducted in the capital Colombo,
the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The surprise announcement came three days after a massive truck
bomb hit the central mountain city of Kandy Sunday morning,
killing at least 16 people and damaging the holiest Buddhist
shrine, the Dalada Maligawa (Tooth Relic Temple).
</P>
<P>
The attack led to a nation-wide outrage towards the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), which was blamed for the attack. The
government on Monday announced that it outlawed the organization
with immediate effect.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the bomb explosion in Kandy, government officials
assured the public that the celebrations in Kandy on February 4
would be carried out as planned.
</P>
<P>
No other details were immediately available.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
