<HEADLINE> Special Items Sent To Earthquake Area For Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 28 (Xinhua) -- Truckloads of special
goods have been delivered to the earthquake-hit area of
Zhangjiakou in north China's Hebei Province for the Spring
Festival.
</P>
<P>
The supplies of pork, beef, mutton, flour, milk powder, and
candies were donated by the people all over the country. According
to a local official in charge of distributing the goods, Sichuan
Province sent 100 tons of pork, and a shipping company in Xiamen
in Fujian Province on the east coast shipped flour, rice, wine,
and sausage on ten trucks to the quake area.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Fusheng Machinery Co. Ltd gave 10 varieties of
dumplings and a company in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region
donated fresh milk, frozen dumplings, and bread.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the goods will mean a lot to the
earthquake victims during the Spring Festival.
</P>
<P>
Some markets have recently re-opened in the quake area. In the
town of Shanjinghe, stalls have been set up along the street, and
one man selling candy said that he can earn about 1,000 to 2,000
yuan a day.
</P>
<P>
One villager said that, with the market re-opening, life in the
quake-stricken area seems to be returning to normal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
