<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elderly People Vulnerable to Murder in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,320 people over the
age of 60 have been murdered in Italy since 1989.
</P>
<P>
A study by the research insitute, Eurispes, which will be
issued on Friday, found that among those old people murdered,
"the victims were increasingly those who are the most
defenseless", women and men over 74.
</P>
<P>
It said the percentage of women over 60 murdered had climbed
from around 23 and 30 percent during the period 1989-92 to 32.40
percent over 1993-1995.
</P>
<P>
The "over-74" category was also at a growing risk and now
accounted for 35 percent of those murdered above 60 years of age,
as opposed to about 30 percent in 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
