<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 28 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin extended sincere Spring
Festival greetings to Chinese people of various ethnic groups, and
compatriots in Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, as well as all
overseas Chinese and foreign nationals of Chinese origin residing
abroad, in an address Tuesday to a Spring Festival gathering
sponsored by the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng said that China's financial and economic
situation remains stable, despite the fact that various other
countries have been adversely affected by the financial crisis in
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony on the eve of the Spring Festival, the
Premier said that China recorded new achievements in reform and
opening, as well as in various other endeavors, during 1997. He
noted that the national economy witnessed steady and rapid growth
accompanied by a low inflation rate, with major economic indices
maintaining promising development trends.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Qiao Shi, chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, in a visit to Guangzhou's Tianhe High-Tech
Development Zone on Sunday, said that Guangdong Province should
provide good conditions for the development of the information
industry.
</P>
<P>
