<HEADLINE> Carlos Flores Sworn in as President of Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Outgoing President Carlos
Roberto Reina Tuesday turned over the presidency to president-
elect Carlos Flores Facusse, who was sworn in as the 74th
president of the constitutional history of Honduras in a ceremony
held at the national stadium in Tegucigalpa.
</P>
<P>
Flores placed his hand on the Constitution of the Republic,
held by his wife Mary Flakes, a U.S. citizen, and took the oath to
govern on behalf of all Hondurans, whatever their politics and to
work to overcome under development and poverty.
</P>
<P>
After the swearing in ceremony, presided over by the new head
of the national congress, Rafael Pineda Ponce, Flores read his 45
minute long speech, the high point of which was when he said, "The
word backward will no longer exist in Honduras because the only
backward thing about us is backward minds."
</P>
<P>
"Our poverty is no excuse because material poverty is the least
important and with determination and hard work we can overcome it
because we are in no way impoverished as far as our history,
resources and even less talent are concerned," said Flores.
</P>
<P>
The new president, who is also a 47 year old industrialist,
thus became the last Honduran president of the 20th century and
the first of the new millennium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
