<HEADLINE> Scot Nicol Hits Top Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Peter Nicol became the first
Briton to top the men's squash rankings as the Professional Squash
Association (PSA) said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old scot has replaced Pakistani ace Jansher Khan,
who first became number one 10 years ago, as world number one.
</P>
<P>
Nicol enjoyed his best year in 1997, winning four titles and
reaching the semifinals in all the PSA events he entered.
</P>
<P>
Nicol is only the fourth player to head the rankings since the
1980s. The others are Jansher, compatriot Jahangir Khan and
Australian Chris Dittmar. 
