<DOCNO> XIE19980128.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Decides to Extend Mandate of MONUA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of
the United Nations today unanimously adopted a resolution,
deciding to extend the mandate of the United Nations Observer
Mission in Angola (MONUA) for a further period of three months
until April 30, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the Security Council reviewed the latest
report by the Secretary-General on Angola. In the resolution, the
Security Council once again expressed its firm commitment to
preserve the unity, sovereignty and territorial integrity of
Angola.
</P>
<P>
The Council urged the Government of Angola and the National
Union for Total independence of Angola (UNITA) to complete the
remaining tasks of the Lusaka Protocol by the end of february
1998.
</P>
<P>
The Council requested the Government of Angola and UNITA, in
cooperation with MONUA, to take appropriate steps, including
through its integrated National Police and Armed Forces, to ensure
an environment of confidence and safety in which the United
Nations and humanitarian personnel may carry out their activities.
</P>
<P>
It called on the Government of Angola and in particular UNITA
to refrain from any action which might undermine the process of
normalization of State administration or lead to renewed tensions.
</P>
<P>
The Council also urged the international community to provide
assistance to facilitate the demobilization and social
reintegration of ex-combatants, demining, the resettlement of
displaced persons and the rehabilitation and reconstruction of the
Angolan economy in order to consolidate the gains in the peace
process.
</P>
<P>
MONUA, which was established in June 1997, is aimed to
succeed the United Nations Angola Verification Mission and
continue to monitor the peace process in the country. It has
2,100 military personnel and its current mandate will expire on
January 31, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980128.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-28 </DATE_TIME>
