<HEADLINE> New York Stock Exchange Bounces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The New York Stock Exchange
rebounded on Tuesday with blue-chips rallying amid encouraging
reports of some major companies' performance in the fourth quarter
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 102.14 points or 1.3
percent to 7,815.08 at the close, according to preliminary data.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's biggest gainer was Disney whose fourth quarter
earnings rose to 755 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Another blue-chip gainer was Ford Motor which saw a 1.8 billion
dollars profit in the last quarter of 1997. Both Ford and Disney
surpassed expectations for their profits.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators also posted gains with the Nastaq
composite index rising 17.45 points to 1,578.91.
</P>
<P>
Advances led declines 17-11 on active volume of 683 million
shares.
</P>
<P>
Today's rally was attributed to large stocks as investors were
still reluctant to buy small-name issues when they were not
certain about the market direction, dealers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
